NEWSWIRE 
Phil Anderson of Australia won the Tour de Romandie road cycling race, 
defending a lead of more than one minute in the 118-mile final leg of the 
six-day event through western Switzerland to Geneva. 
Anderson led from the opening road stage of the 539-mile tour, which he won for 
the first time with a total time of 21 hours 37 minutes 6 seconds. 
Gilles Delion of France, trailing Anderson's aggregate by 1:04, edged Britain's 
Robert Millar for second place. 
